RACE.RACE_TEXT: EMERALD DOWNS RACE 1 6F Dirt CR: 56. Maiden Claiming Purse 10000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD. Three Year Olds, 121 lbs.; Older, 125 lbs. Claiming Price $8,000, if for $7,000, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: LUVAHAPPYENDING was allowed to settle, swung out 4-wide to launch her bid nearing the quarter pole, took the lead approaching the eighth pole and proved best under strong handling. PERCY'S SIS broke in to bump with HASTA LUEGO, then vied for the lead from between horses, responded during the drive and held on gamely for the place. FLYING SYLVIA was reserved off the early pace, moved up strongly on along the inside on the turn, steadied nearing the quarter pole lacking room, angled in entering the stretch and then had to angle out nearing the eighth pole when in tight and finished strongly when clear. BABY MARTINI was unhurried early, rallied four-wide into the stretch and passed tiring rivals. PISTA GIRL disputed the pace to the stretch while racing three-wide and weakened. HASTA LUEGO was bumped at the start, then dueled for the lead to the stretch from along the inside and tired.

ENTRY.COMMENT: reserved, inside turn, steadied 1/4, in tight 1/8, rallied

ENTRY.NAME: Percy's Sis
ENTRY.COMMENT: broke in, bumped, vied 2-wide, held gamely

AIN'T NO SISSY vied for the lead from between horses, came out slightly to bump at the wire and finished well in a steady effort. NIGHT TO REMEMBER was allowed to settle in stride, was in tight nearing the quarter pole running up on horses, angled in nearing the three-sixteenths pole and finished willingly while being bumped at the wire. ABOVE THE REST was off a step slow, then rushed up to duel for the lead from along the inside to the stretch and tired. UHTREDSONOFUHTRED dropped back early, raced four-wide and failed to menace. THE STEWARDS CONDUCTED AN INQUIRY INTO THE INCIDENT IN DEEP STRETCH BUT AFTEW VIEWING THE FILMS DETERMNED THE BUMPING OCCURED AT THE WIRE.
